<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-813] no assignments to literals</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-813</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Definitely!  Whether we can do this inside the Antlr grammar, or we add &lt;br/&gt;
a validation check to the Groovy AST verifier (which has a few checks &lt;br/&gt;
in it already) I don&apos;t much mind, but we definitely need to outlaw &lt;br/&gt;
these examples.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On 9 Apr 2005, at 13:21, Dierk Koenig wrote:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Currently Groovy allows&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &apos;aaa&apos; = &apos;bbb&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &quot;aaa&quot; = &quot;bbb&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; /aaa/ = /bbb/&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; null = new Object()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; 0 = 1&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; 0f = 1f&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; \u0000 = \u0001&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; // questionable&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; [] = new Object()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;:&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; = new Object()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; 1..2 = new Object()&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; this makes it harder to write safe boolean tests, e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;  if (null == a)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; instead of&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;  if (a == null)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; to mitigate the risk of a missing =, e.g&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;  if (null = a)&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; should not compile.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; I think this should be possible by changing&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; only the grammar file.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; cheers&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Mittie&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;James&lt;br/&gt;
